headlines.description: — Aaron Holiday scored 22 points, brother Justin Holiday had 21 and the short-handed Indiana Pacers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 141-137 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday brothers lead Pacers past Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal returned from a five-game absence and scored 26 points, Russell Westbrook had his 20th triple-double of the season and the Washington Wizards made a season-best 19 3-pointers in a 131-116 win over the Orlando Magic on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal, Westbrook lead Wizards past Magic 131-116

events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown had 32 points and 10 rebounds, and the Boston Celtics rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the New York Knicks 101-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 32, Celtics hold on for 101-99 win over Knicks

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant returned from a 23-game absence to spark Brooklyn's most explosive half of the season, finishing with 17 points and perfect shooting in the Nets' 139-111 rout of the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant's perfect return fuels Nets' 139-111 rout of Pelicans

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen scored 17 of his season-high 30 points in a dominant third quarter, leading the Memphis Grizzlies to a 131-113 win over the short-handed Atlanta Hawks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Allen has 30 to help streaking Grizzlies beat Hawks, 131-113

headlines.description: — John Wall had 31 points and seven assists in his return from injury, and the Houston Rockets snapped a five-game skid with a 102-93 win over the Dallas Mavericks on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wall scores 31, Rockets end skid with 102-93 win over Mavs

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jalen McDaniels had a career-high 21 points in his second career start to help the Charlotte Hornets beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 113-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McDaniels has career-high 21 points, Hornets beat Thunder

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 25 points, 10 assists and nine rebounds to help the surging Denver Nuggets beat the San Antonio Spurs 106-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic scores 25 points, Nuggets beat Spurs 106-96

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 35 points, Chris Paul added 29 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Utah Jazz 117-113 in overtime Wednesday night in an entertaining matchup between the top two teams in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Paul lead Suns to 117-113 OT win over Jazz
